{
  "esm": "0.4.0",
  "metadata": {
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciData.jl contributors",
      "EarthSciModels migration (esm-49vi)"
    ],
    "created": "2026-05-29T00:00:00Z",
    "description": "2-D bilinear interpolator for the mean dry surface pressure-thickness (delp_dry_surface) over the CONUS NEI2016 domain. Loaded from mean_domian_delp_dry_surface.jld2 at EarthSciData.jl commit 830435a. Grid: lon in [-125.0, -66.875] step 0.625 (94 pts) x lat in [25.0, 49.0] step 0.5 (49 pts). Used in NEI2016MonthlyEmis to convert flux emissions to mixing ratios via: mixing_ratio = flux / (g0_100 x delp), where g0_100 = 100/g0 ~ 10.197 kg/m2. The gt-p3ep gap is resolved by embedding the 94x49 precomputed table as interp.bilinear with flat extrapolation.",
    "name": "nei_delp_dry_surface_itp",
    "references": [
      {
        "citation": "EarthSciData.jl@830435a065f27e99f10bba91107ca1730322cc6b:src/nei2016monthly.jl. delp_dry_surface_itp(lon, lat) registered as a symbolic function; data from mean_domian_delp_dry_surface.jld2."
      },
      {
        "citation": "US EPA National Emissions Inventory 2016. Monthly gridded emissions, 12US1 12-km Lambert Conformal Conic grid. https://gaftp.epa.gov/Air/emismod/2016/v1/gridded/monthly_netCDF/"
      }
    ],
    "tags": [
      "earthscidata",
      "nei2016",
      "registered_function",
      "surface_pressure",
      "delp",
      "lookup_table",
      "interp-bilinear",
      "emissions"
    ]
  },
